d":"italic_en","text":"ten thousand cubits:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three miles of the Háshimee measure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., accord. to the Bári' and the T [&c.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twenty-five bow-shots; twenty-five times the measure termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galowapN","text_ar":"غَلْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three miles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirty bow-shots reckoning the bow-shot as four hundred cubits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixty bow-shots reckoning the bow-shot as two hundred cubits:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maylN","text_ar":"مَيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the ancient Greeks said that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three miles, reckoning these"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as about sixty bow-shots"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the shorter measure mentioned above"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb in the present art.:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six miles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L: [but this is app. a mistake occasioned by finding it expl. as consisting of sixty bow-shots and supposing these to be bow-shots of four hundred cubits each:]) it is [said to be] from the same word as signifying “ rest, ” or “ ease; ” (K, TA;) because, when a man walks the distance thus called, he sits down, and rests: or, accord. to the Msb, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farosaxapN","text_ar":"فَرْسَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ width; ” the word having this meaning, however, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faro$axapN","text_ar":"فَرْشَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [the truth is, that] it is a Pers. word ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farosanoG","text_ar":"فَرْسَنْگ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], arabicized: (S, A:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAsixu","text_ar":"فَرَاسِخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, Msb.) The other meanings of this word, not mentioned by J, may have been regarded by him as not of established authority. (TA.) ―         -b2-  It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An opening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intervening space, between two things."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing in which is no opening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intervening space:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though having two contr. significations. (K.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is lasting and abundant, that does not cease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come to an end."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long time"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the night"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinotaZarotuka","text_ar":"اِنْتَظَرْتُكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farosaxFA","text_ar":"فَرْسَخًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I looked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waited, for thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have looked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long time"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEap","text_ar":"سَاعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K, TA) of the day: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the night and of the day: pl. as above. (TA.) ―         -b7-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interval,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between stillness and motion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stillness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) a meaning mentioned by more than one of the authorities respecting strange words. (TA.) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","TA","S","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}